  "uid": "Burkitt_Medal_1",
  "intro": "The Burkitt Medal is awarded annually by the British Academy in recognition of special service to Biblical Studies. Awards alternate between Hebrew Bible studies (odd years) and New Testament studies (even years). It was established in 1923 and has been awarded to many notable theologians. It is named in honour of Francis Crawford Burkitt."
